---
permalink: /privacy/
title: Privacy Policy
description: How ArcadeBloom handles data. We run a directory — we do not require an account to browse.
---
{% extends 'base.njk' %}

{% block content %}
<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <nav class="text-sm text-white/60 mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Privacy</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-white/50 text-sm mb-8">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <div class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">1. No account required</h2>
            <p>ArcadeBloom is a directory. You can browse, search, and read every page without creating an account or providing any personal information.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2. Analytics</h2>
            <p>We use privacy-respecting analytics to understand aggregate traffic (which pages are read, roughly where visitors come from). We do not build individual user profiles or sell data.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">3. Cookies</h2>
            <p>Any cookies are limited to essential functionality (such as remembering your search query) and aggregate analytics. We do not use cookies for cross-site tracking or ad targeting.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">4. When you leave ArcadeBloom</h2>
            <p>The "Play" links send you to third-party sites. Those sites have their own privacy policies which govern what they collect once you arrive. We have no control over and take no responsibility for their practices.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">5. How we count Play clicks (aggregate only)</h2>
            <p>When you click a Play button, ArcadeBloom records a single anonymous count so we can tell which games are actually being played. The only data sent is: the game's slug, a coarse referral bucket (for example "google" or "direct"), and a coarse device bucket (desktop / tablet / mobile). This is combined into a daily total per game.</p>
            <p>We do <strong>not</strong> record your IP address, any cookie or account identifier, your full referrer URL, your user agent, or any cross-site identifier. The click is sent the moment you press Play and nothing about you personally is kept.</p>
            <p>This first-party click count is separate from any advertising (see below). It is anonymous aggregate measurement and does not track you across sites.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">6. Contact</h2>
            <p>Questions about privacy? See the <a href="/contact/" class="underline hover:text-white">contact page</a>.</p>
        </section>
    </div>

</div>
{% endblock %}
